    <briefdescription>
<para>Defines a style for repeating a 3x3 tile pattern across a rectangle. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The 9-tile layout uses this arrangement: top-left, top, top-right, left, center, right, bottom-left, bottom, bottom-right.</para>
<para>Optionally, 7 additional tiles can be provided for degenerate rectangles: single-row left, single-row center, single-row right, single-column top, single-column center, single-column bottom, and the single-cell tile. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
